May 30, 2017
HomeCompany News & Financial SectorClariVest Asset Management LLC Increases Position in Universal Forest Products, Inc. (UFPI)


ClariVest Asset Management LLC Increases Position in Universal Forest Products, Inc. (UFPI)



By Rosalyn Hughes
Company News & Financial Sector
 0 Comments










ClariVest Asset Management LLC increased its position in shares of  Universal Forest Products, Inc. (NASDAQ:UFPI) by 10.3% during the first quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The fund owned 81,911 shares of the construction company’s stock after buying an additional 7,628 shares during the period. ClariVest Asset Management LLC owned about 0.40% of Universal Forest Products worth $8,070,000 at the end of the most recent quarter. 
A number of other large investors also recently made changes to their positions in the stock. Russell Investments Group Ltd. bought a new stake in shares of  Universal Forest Products during the fourth quarter worth $12,012,000.  Northern Trust Corp increased its stake in shares of  Universal Forest Products by 0.8% in the third quarter. Northern Trust Corp now owns 345,079 shares of the construction company’s stock worth $33,986,000 after buying an additional 2,569 shares during the last quarter.  GSA Capital Partners LLP increased its stake in shares of  Universal Forest Products by 17.9% in the fourth quarter. GSA Capital Partners LLP now owns 12,270 shares of the construction company’s stock worth $1,254,000 after buying an additional 1,860 shares during the last quarter.  Renaissance Group LLC acquired a new stake in shares of  Universal Forest Products during the first quarter worth about $331,000.  Finally, KCG Holdings Inc. increased its stake in shares of  Universal Forest Products by 197.2% in the third quarter. KCG Holdings Inc. now owns 7,628 shares of the construction company’s stock worth $751,000 after buying an additional 5,061 shares during the last quarter. Institutional investors and hedge funds own  81.12% of the company’s stock. 
                  Get Universal Forest Products Inc. alerts:               

Universal Forest Products, Inc. (NASDAQ:UFPI) traded up 0.38% during mid-day trading on Monday, reaching $90.71. 72,884 shares of the company were exchanged. Universal Forest Products, Inc. has a 1-year low of $82.35 and a 1-year high of $110.97. The company has a market capitalization of $1.86 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 18.01 and a beta of 1.70. The company has a 50 day moving average of $93.21 and a 200-day moving average of $98.44. 
Universal Forest Products (NASDAQ:UFPI) last issued its earnings results on Tuesday, April 18th. The construction company reported $1.03 EPS for the quarter, hitting analysts’ consensus estimates of $1.03. Universal Forest Products had a net margin of 3.27% and a return on equity of 12.31%. The company had revenue of $846.10 million for the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $812.57 million. During the same period in the previous year, the firm earned $0.95 earnings per share. Universal Forest Products’s quarterly revenue was up 24.0% compared to the same quarter last year.  On average, equities research analysts forecast that  Universal Forest Products, Inc. will post $5.87 EPS for the current year. 







The company also recently announced a semiannual dividend, which will be paid on Thursday, June 15th. Shareholders of record on Thursday, June 1st will be paid a dividend of $0.45 per share. This represents a yield of 0.94%. The ex-dividend date of this dividend is Tuesday, May 30th. Universal Forest Products’s dividend payout ratio (DPR) is presently 18.44%. 
