A number of brokerages have recently issued reports on UFPI. ValuEngine raised shares of Universal Forest Products from a “hold” rating to a “buy” rating in a research report on Thursday, May 11th. Zacks Investment Research raised shares of Universal Forest Products from a “sell” rating to a “buy” rating and set a $110.00 price objective for the company in a research report on Friday, March 17th.
In other Universal Forest Products news, VP Charles Scott Greene sold 2,475 shares of Universal Forest Products stock in a transaction dated Thursday, March 16th. The shares were sold at an average price of $99.49, for a total transaction of $246,237.75. Following the transaction, the vice president now directly owns 5,298 shares of the company’s stock, valued at $527,098.02. The sale was disclosed in a legal filing with the Securities & Exchange Commission, which is available through the SEC website. Also, Director Michael G. Wooldridge bought 500 shares of Universal Forest Products stock in a transaction on Thursday, March 2nd. The shares were purchased at an average cost of $99.24 per share, for a total transaction of $49,620.00. Following the completion of the purchase, the director now directly owns 1,808 shares of the company’s stock, valued at $179,425.92. The disclosure for this purchase can be found here. 3.50% of the stock is owned by insiders. 
Universal Forest Products Company Profile
Universal Forest Products, Inc is a holding company. The Company, through its subsidiaries, supplies wood, wood composite and other products to three primary markets, such as retail, construction and industrial. Its segments include North, South, West, Alternative Materials, International, idX Holdings, Inc (idX) and Corporate divisions.
