Class of 1990 


University of Waterloo

                  University of Waterloo is home to world-changing research and inspired teaching. At the hub of a growing network of global partnerships, Waterloo will shape the future by building bridges with industry and between disciplines, institutions and communities.                




Master of Business Administration Degree 


Queen’s University - School of Business

                  Queen's School of Business is one of the world's premier business schools, with a faculty team renowned for its academic credentials and business experience. The School has earned international recognition for its innovative approaches to business education and has been a pioneer in the areas of team-based and experiential learning.                





 Career History



Founder

                                    2006 - Current                


ClariVest Asset Management LLC


                  ClariVest Asset Management uses economically sensible stock selection criterion in conjunction with state-of-the-art risk control techniques to exploit market inefficiencies arising from behaviorally-based reactions to company and market-wide growth and contraction cycles. The firm manages domestic, international, and global equity portfolios across the market-cap spectrum.                




Quantitative Analyst

                                    Prior                


Putnam Investments Ltd.


                  Putnam Investments is an active, research-driven manager which provides specialist products tailored to investment styles (growth, value, income), fiscal requirements (taxable, tax-free), regional allocation, risk, diversification, or time horizon.The firm is a long-term, value-oriented, conservative manager which focuses on consistent results and follows a bottom-up approach to select equities. They invest across all major equity and fixed-income asset classes, and offer products across the spectrum of traditional long-only, quantitative, and alternative strategies.Putnam Investments conducts regular company visits, seeking to invest in companies with a reasonable p/e ratio, sound business models, a steady revenue stream and some pricing power. Quantitative analysis involves modelling future performances based on past trends. Regional considerations include the political, economic, and interest rate outlook of each country. Sectorial analysis integrates the short and long-term factors influencing industry, and the credit worthiness of security issuers.                




Partner

                                    Prior                


Genus Capital Management


                  Genus Capital Management manages conventional domestic and international long-only equity strategies, long/short and market-neutral strategies, and socially screened investment options.All of the firm's equity strategies employ a style-diversified approach that combines elements of value, growth and quality. The firm employs proprietary quantitative and qualitative research that seeks to identify under-valued companies with superior fundamentals and earnings growth. Their research also considers price to earnings, price to cash flow and price to sales ratios with indicators of fundamental growth and profitability, including expected growth, earnings forecast revisions and returns on equity. Genus seeks to add value from stock selection.The firm's Core Canadian Equity product is an actively managed, core portfolio that holds 60 to 85 securities. It is style-diversified and blends six fundamentals of value, growth and quality. The portfolio is well-diversified across all sectors, industries and styles.Genus' Canadian 130/30 Equity product is an actively managed portfolio that includes long and short positions. The strategy seeks to enhance the alpha opportunity of a long-only portfolio by partially relaxing the short constraints within a risk-controlled framework. The portfolio is well-diversified across all sectors, industries, and styles.Their Core US Equity product is an actively managed, style-diversified portfolio that combines elements of value, growth and quality. Securities are selected from companies that are included in the S&P 500 Index. The portfolio is well-diversified across all sectors and industries.Genus' Core International Equity product is an actively managed, style-diversified portfolio that invests in companies that are included in the MSCI EAFE Index. The portfolio is well-diversified across all countries, sectors and industries.The firm's Market Neutral Equity product is an actively managed, style-diversified portfolio that seeks to provide consistent long term capital appreciation with low correlation to the broader market and less volatility than equity indexes. The portfolio holds long and short positions in equity securities that are traded on the TSX and in the MSCI World Index. The net exposure to equity markets, industries, sectors is typically close to zero.Genus' Biosphere Plus Canadian Equity product is an actively managed, socially screened portfolio that holds 60 to 85 securities. Stocks are selected based on social and environmental considerations. The portfolio is style diversified and blends attributes of value, growth and quality.The firm's bond portfolios are managed by Montreal-based Addenda Capital. Addenda's core fixed-income style uses multiple investment strategies to manage of bonds. They use a top-down approach to develop economic and market forecasts. They offer a variety of fixed-income investment strategies, including interest rate anticipation, yield curve management, trading among sectors, individual security selection and credit analysis. This approach combines a 12-month overall strategy with a shorter-term tactical strategy that seeks to take advantage of market fluctuations to add substantial value to client portfolios.                




Lead Portfolio Manager

                                    Prior - 2006                


Nicholas-Applegate Capital Management LLC


                  Nicholas-Applegate Capital Management employs a forward-thinking, change-focused investment philosophy to create domestic and international portfolios across fundamental and systematic equity, income and growth strategies. The firm's investment approach seeks to identify points of inflection that could lead to strong price appreciation and to invest in a timely manner to maximize return potential. The firm's range of investment strategies include domestic, global, international and specialty portfolios. Each portfolio follows one of two approaches: traditional or model-driven (systematic). Nicholas-Applegate tends to invest in the stocks of companies in the electronic technology, health technology, technology services, consumer non-durables and finance sectors. The firm invests globally, across all market-caps. Nicholas-Applegate maintains a medium turnover rate.                





